                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/270.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-23T14:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1912—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Press reports that the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Maryland</hi> is now on the way
                    to Los Mochis are giving Minister Foreign Affairs much concern. He says Mexican
                    Government has no objection to Americans there being taken away by the United
                    States, but on account of effect upon public opinion earnestly hopes that vessel
                    may be revenue cutter or transport.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
